    "body": "<!-- .github/pull_request_template.md -->\r\n\r\n## 📌 Description\r\n\r\nIn 0.6.7, the norm kernels switched from the CUDA JIT path to the CuTe DSL path by\r\ndefault. The CuTe DSL kernels emit `griddepcontrol.wait` / `griddepcontrol.launch_dependents` PTX when `enable_pdl=True`, which requires `.target sm_90` or higher.\r\n\r\nFix: Add ensures a clamp such that `enable_pdl=False` on unsupported hardware, while preserving the existing behavior for None (auto-detect) and False (opt-out).\r\n\r\nAffected APIs\r\n- `rmsnorm()`\r\n- `rmsnorm_quant()`\r\n- `fused_add_rmsnorm()`\r\n- `fused_add_rmsnorm_quant()`\r\n- `gemma_rmsnorm()`\r\n- `gemma_fused_add_rmsnorm()`\r\n\r\nPDL Behavior summary\r\n\r\n\r\n| enable_pdl arg | HW supports PDL (SM>=90) | Before (0.6.7) | After (fix)\r\n-- | -- | -- | --\r\nNone | Yes (Hopper+) | PDL enabled | PDL enabled\r\nNone | No (Ampere) | PDL disabled | PDL disabled\r\nTrue | Yes (Hopper+) | PDL enabled | PDL enabled\r\n**True** | **No (Ampere)** | **ptxas crash** | **PDL disabled**\r\nFalse | Yes (Hopper+) | PDL disabled | PDL disabled\r\nFalse | No (Ampere) | PDL disabled | PDL disabled\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- What does this PR do? Briefly describe the changes and why they’re needed. -->\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Related Issues\r\n\r\n#2920\r\n\r\n<!-- Link any related issues here -->\r\n\r\n## 🚀 Pull Request Checklist\r\n\r\nThank you for contributing to FlashInfer! Before we review your pull request, please make sure the following items are complete.\r\n\r\n### ✅ Pre-commit Checks\r\n\r\n- [x] I have installed `pre-commit` by running `pip install pre-commit` (or used your preferred method).\r\n- [x] I have installed the hooks with `pre-commit install`.\r\n- [x] I have run the hooks manually with `pre-commit run --all-files` and fixed any reported issues.\r\n\r\n> If you are unsure about how to set up `pre-commit`, see [the pre-commit documentation](https://pre-commit.com/).\r\n\r\n## 🧪 Tests\r\n\r\n- [ ] Tests have been added or updated as needed.\r\n- [ ] All tests are passing (`unittest`, etc.).\r\n\r\n## Reviewer Notes\r\n\r\n<!-- Optional: anything you'd like reviewers to focus on, concerns, etc. -->\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n* **Optimizations**\r\n  * Improved device capability detection for normalization operations, enabling better automatic selection of optimal execution paths based on hardware compatibility.\r\n\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
